                    <p>Hello there! My name is Evan R Bogart. I'm a recent DePaul University graduate, where I majored in Interactive and Social Media (ISM for short) with a Development Concentration. Most of my work on this site will be comprised of projects I worked on throughout my 2 &frac12; years at DePaul University. I consider myself a fun-loving coder, and an admirer of design - specifically web/application/software design! Besides coding I enjoy playing video games, watching esports/sports in general, hiking, fishing, and hanging out with friends and family.</p>
                    <p>As an ISM major with a Development Concentration, I focused a lot on the front-end. ISM mostly taught me about modern UI/UX design principles and heuristics, which can be very useful to know when evaulating, designing, or developing a site/application. I am very comfortable developing front-end solutions and fully responsive websites using HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript/jQuery. I have extensive use with Bootstrap, and I'll tend to heavily utilize utility classes to setup a quick and easy grid system.</p> 
                    <p>I love Ruby-on-Rails! It's the first MVC framework I learned for web development, and I feel fully confident in coding the front-end for a Ruby-on-Rails web application. I know my way around the Ruby-on-Rails MVC framework, and I'm not scared to utilize the whole spectrum of the framework to correctly implement partials, views, and layouts. Though, when it comes down to it all, I fell in love with this framework because it allows me to work with ".erb" files - my exact initials. &#128516;</p>   
